text.tspan: Share of adult women overweight or obese vs. daily caloric supply, 2013 to 2014
The share of adult women defined as overweight or obese, measured as the percentage of women with a body mass
index (BMI) greater than 25, versus the daily caloric supply, measured in kilocalories per person per day. BMI is a
person's weight (in kilograms) divided by their height (in meters) squared.
Share of women overweight or obese
Data source: Prevalence of weight categories in females - NCDRisC (2017); Our World in Data based on the Food and Agriculture
Organization of the United Nations & historical sources
